5000|$|<b>Algophobia</b> is a phobia of pain - an {{abnormal}} and persistent fear of pain {{that is far}} more powerful {{than that of a}} normal person. <b>Algophobia</b> is much more common in elderly people. It can be treated with behavioral therapy and anti-anxiety medication. The term comes from the ἄλγος, álgos, [...] "pain" [...] and , phóbos, [...] "fear".|$|E
50|$|The Fear of Pain Questionnaire (currently the FPQ-III) {{has been}} used to test for <b>Algophobia</b> in the past and was found to have good {{internal}} consistency and test-retest reliability.|$|E

